# Meaning of @ symbol in file list
The @ symbol at the end of a file or directory's permission string
indicates that the file has extended attributes. 
These extended attributes are additional metadata stored alongside the
file, which can include information like Finder icon settings, file
encoding, security status (such as quarantine data), or custom
user-defined data. 
The presence of the @ symbol is specific to macOS and is not used in
standard Unix/Linux systems.





